e PCR tube with 10 \u03bcL sterile deionized water and transfer it to the 1.5 mL tube. Mix briefly. Final volume ~ 30 \u03bcL<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#bd10e0","section_duration":86400,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1214323,"guid":"FD70CFF0E61611EB9993CDE2C86D7EF8","previous_id":1214322,"previous_guid":"07409720E61411EB9993CDE2C86D7EF8","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"107F95253AB047EE997E90A29E0D3231","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Quantification and quality check"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"D7815C208C264EB3A6907AC10E81F2DB","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Quantify the amount of DNA using 1 \u03bcL of the amplification reaction and the HS dsDNA Qubit kit<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Quantify 1 \u03bcL of the water control reaction as well<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":7200,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1214324,"guid":"3070B0A0E61711EB9993CDE2C86D7EF8","previous_id":1214323,"previous_guid":"FD70CFF0E61611EB9993CDE2C86D7EF8","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"F3155AAED18648738DB72561BF86B54D","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Quantification and quality check"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F2694F3ECB5346F9B8B739C6FC1AA194","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Depending on the yield, load 50 - 100 ng of amplified DNA in one lane of a 1% agarose gel in 1X TAE. Load ALL the water control reaction in another well. Load 4 \u03bcL of the 1 Kb Plus ladder in a separate lane<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Run the gel at 140 V for 30 min<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"